Your Honor,

I, David Lambert, stand before you today to plead guilty to the charge of driving whilst disqualified. I am deeply remorseful for my actions and understand the gravity of my offense. I am aware that I failed to adhere to the court's previous order and for that, I am truly sorry.

I must admit, in my shameful act, I failed to consider the consequences of my actions. It was a momentary lapse in judgment that allowed me to overlook the fact that I was disqualified from driving. I foolishly got into the car and drove to the supermarket, ignoring the restrictions placed upon me.

I would like to express my sincere regret for my behavior. I understand that my disregard for the law is not only a breach of trust but also a disregard for the safety of others on the road. I accept full responsibility for my actions and the negative impact it may have caused.

Although I am now faced with the consequences of my choices, I would like to assure the court that this is an isolated incident. As a 55-year-old individual with no criminal record, I have always strived to abide by the law. It is with great disappointment in myself that I find myself in this position today.

During these past few months, I have taken the time to reflect on my actions and the potential harm I have caused. I have come to realize the importance of being accountable for one's actions. I am committed to making amends, both for myself and for the community at large.

In an effort to prevent a recurrence of such an offense, I am willing to take the necessary steps to improve myself. I am open to participating in courses that will enhance my understanding of the responsibilities of a driver and the importance of following the law. By gaining this knowledge, I aim to become a more responsible and law-abiding citizen.

Your Honor, I would like to emphasize that I have already experienced significant suffering as a result of my actions. The shame and regret that I carry with me are constant reminders of the harm I have caused. I assure the court that this experience has been a wake-up call, and I am determined to learn from my mistakes.

Finally, I would like to highlight my prior contributions to society. Throughout my life, I have always strived to be a productive member of the community. I have been committed to my family, my work, and fostering positive relationships with those around me. It is my hope that you will consider this aspect of my character while determining an appropriate sentence.

In conclusion, I acknowledge the seriousness of my offense and the disappointment it has caused. I plead guilty and accept the consequences that come with it. I am sincerely remorseful for my actions and am committed to making amends and preventing any future transgressions. I humbly request the court's leniency and the opportunity to demonstrate that I have learned from this experience.

Thank you for your attention, Your Honor.

