Your Honor,

I, David Lambert, stand before you today to plead guilty to the charge of driving whilst disqualified. I am deeply remorseful for my actions and understand the gravity of my offense. I am aware that I failed to adhere to the court's previous order and for that, I am truly sorry.

I must admit, in my shameful act, I failed to consider the consequences of my actions. It was a momentary lapse in judgment that allowed me to overlook the fact that I was disqualified from driving. I foolishly got into the car and drove to the supermarket, ignoring the restrictions placed upon me.

I would like to express my sincere regret for my behavior. I understand that my disregard for the law is not only a breach of trust but also a disregard for the safety of others on the road. I accept full responsibility for my actions and the negative impact it may have caused.

Your Honor, I want to assure you that I am committed to learning from this experience and preventing any future transgressions. As a 55-year-old individual with no criminal record, I have always strived to abide by the law. It is with great disappointment in myself that I find myself in this position today.

During these past few months, I have taken the time to reflect on my actions and the potential harm I have caused. I have come to realize the importance of being accountable for one's actions. I am willing to take the necessary steps to improve myself and ensure that such an offense does not happen again.

In an effort to demonstrate my commitment to change, I am open to participating in courses that will enhance my understanding of the responsibilities of a driver and the importance of following the law. By gaining this knowledge, I aim to become a more responsible and law-abiding citizen.

